😭it seems like a lot but it’s not, watch as I incorporate all 4 techniques into 1 braid!! 

1. Add in small pieces. 

This gets a clean braid with no lumps. Knotless braids are technically feed in braids. You’re feeding the hair into a braid. If you feed in too large it’ll be a noticeable flaw. 

2.  Immediately add hair. 

Especially thin hair, you need an anchor technique to ensure security. Without security the roots get old or the braids become so heavy overtime causing breakage in some areas. 

3. Add hair to the backbone of the braid. 

Listen I’m telling you !! This is the secret technique if you’re trying to tuck!! When you tuck the natural hair the braids last longer regardless the texture. 

4. Only add hair to 1 side. 

This technique is less work because it gives you enough time to judge if you need to add more hair or not. When you frequently add hair to a knotless braid it grows. I may grow faster than you need it too. Keep your sizes somewhat consistent.
